iece of dough into an oval shape (approx. 35 x 25 cm), then transfer onto prepared baking trays. Pinch edges of dough to create a border, to help contain toppings during baking. Set aside while making toppings."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Roast beef and mushroom topping"},{"content":"Place garlic into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add sour cream, ½ tsp of the salt and ¼ tsp of the pepper and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Spread mixture evenly over pizza bases."},{"content":"Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh roast beef, whiskey and honey into it. Add ½ tsp salt, ¼ tsp pepper, sweet paprika and hot paprika and stir to combine well. Spread mixture evenly over pizza bases."},{"content":"Place a separate bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh mushrooms into it. Add oil, ¼ tsp salt, ¼ tsp pepper, thyme and lemon zest, then stir to combine. Spread mixture evenly over pizza bases. Bake for 20-25 minutes (220°C). Sprinkle with spring onions\/shallots and shaved Parmesan cheese, before slicing and serving."}],"basicInfo":["medium","15m","1h 40m","8 portions"]}